Finding peak in price

  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(550, 650), breaks = seq(550,650, 5))

Note: Peak at 605 being the mode Using a function to calculate the mode (from tutorialspoint.com)

# Create the function.
getmode <- function(v) {
   uniqv <- unique(v)
   uniqv[which.max(tabulate(match(v, uniqv)))]
}
# Calculate the mode using the user function.
result <- getmode(diamonds$price)
print(result)
[1] 605
